The daily number of cases had been below 1,000 from late May until last Friday, hitting a low of 786 on June 2. In the last 24 hours, 15 people died, bringing total fatalities to 4,807, the ministry data showed. There have been a total 178,239 cases of COVID-19 in Turkey. (Reporting by Daren Butler. Editing by Jane Merriman) Please note you must be a Maverick Insider to comment. Sign up here or sign in if you are already an Insider.